about.summary: Allows users to conduct multivariate distance matrix regression using analytic p-values and compute measures of effect size. For details on the method, see McArtor, Lubke, & Bergeman (2017) <doi:10.1007/s11336-016-9527-8>.

name: r-mdmr
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.5.1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-mdmr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/MDMR_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/MDMR/MDMR_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 5d18c3379ca6e7762f218c2c9fc8c9b49aa194acce5624c3ef58cb7b683f65df

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 2
  noarch: generic

  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]

  host:
    - r-base
    - r-compquadform
    - r-car
    - r-lme4

  run:
    - r-base
    - r-compquadform
    - r-car
    - r-lme4

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('MDMR')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('MDMR')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://github.com/dmcartor/mdmr
  license: GPL (>= 2)
  summary: Allows users to conduct multivariate distance matrix regression using analytic p-values
    and compute measures of effect size. For details on the method, see McArtor, Lubke,
    & Bergeman (2017) <doi:10.1007/s11336-016-9527-8>.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - mcornwell1957
